{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1783137675,"nonce":"yAgo425/3TcrXLRld0pD4Cb3qMU=","message":"Update: PR #74 now introspects SQLite views (name + columns from sqlite_master + PRAGMA table_info, empty projection). So the removal/rename/name-collision half of this bug is RESOLVED there — a view removed from the desired model now produces a DropView and no longer lingers.\n\nRemaining scope for this bug (still deferred):\n- Churn: the core diff (diff_views_global) always re-emits CreateView for a body-unknown (empty-projection) view, so a present view re-applies on every plan (cross-backend; PG/MySQL use CREATE OR REPLACE).\n- Trigger wipe: on SQLite that re-apply is DROP VIEW + CREATE VIEW, which drops user INSTEAD OF triggers.\nMaking an unchanged view a true no-op needs view-column-type canonicalization (or body/rendered-SQL comparison) in the core diff; trigger preservation needs the executor to capture/replay triggers around the drop.","files":null}]}